    <bug_when>2012-12-30 18:19:08 +0200</bug_when>
    <thetext>I&apos;m using the Git development version that I update from time to time.  Currently the version is 2.1.0_dev+0484ae7

I&apos;ve noticed a kind of asymmetry in the verse scrolling that I don&apos;t think is intentional and doesn&apos;t really make sense.

If I type &quot;ctrl-v&quot; to scroll down the verses in a chapter, when I get to the end of the chapter it stops with the last verse of the chapter. However, when I hit &quot;ctrl-shift-v&quot; to scroll up, when I get to the first verse and hit it again it will scroll to the last verse of the previous chapter.

I actually like this latter behavior because chapter breaks are artificial. But at least it should do one or the other, because if I scroll accidentally into the previous chapter and then try to scroll back with &quot;ctrl-v&quot; it won&apos;t; it just stays at the last verse of the previous chapter. I have to use the chapter-scroll mechanism and that&apos;s inconvenient.

Actually I&apos;ve mapped the second shortcuts in the Bible windows to the arrow keys, which is why it&apos;s inconvenient (I can&apos;t just use the arrow keys to scroll back and forth because it gets &quot;stuck&quot;), but the same behavior exists whether or not there&apos;s any such mapping.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
